added.title: Extra, So Extra
added.description: Babs realizes Acme Loo's school paper has closed so she starts a new one with her pal Sweetie. But when Plucky starts a gossipy tabloid to compete against them, which paper will come out on top?

added.title: Tooney Ball Lights
added.description: Buster and Sweetie join the Tooney Ball team during Electives Week while Babs and Plucky tackle the basics in Anvils 101, leaving Hamton on a journey to fix his indecisiveness.

added.title: Fun Fight at the Oh Cake Corral
added.description: It's definitely no cake walk as Campers compete in the ultimate island bake-off. A very special guest judge even stops by for a bite!

added.title: Haulin' n' Ballin'
added.description: The fate of Priya and Caleb's relationship hangs in the balance as Zee struggles to keep a secret. And it all plays out during a brutal game of human pinball.

added.title: Breaking Up Is Hard To Do
added.description: Caleb is desperate to put his relationship with Priya back together while the campers tear apart the largest objects they can find.

added.title: Circling The Drain
added.description: Julia gets between Caleb and Priya during the most painful memory game of all time.

added.title: Crowbar Jones: Origins
added.description: Grizz pitches his Crowbar Jones prequel film to Nom Nom, hoping Nom Nom will agree to appear in the movie.

added.title: Hot Sauce
added.description: A quest for their favorite hot sauce causes the Bears to get involved with a sting operation.

added.title: Mom App
added.description: Hoping to finally get the mom-experience, the Bears use an app that'll bring a mom right to their door.

added.title: Family Troubles
added.description: Baby Grizz lives on the set of a sitcom in which he stars. But when a cooler kid joins the cast, Grizz feels threatened.

added.title: Best Bears
added.description: The Bears must complete their Best-Man duties on the day of Darrell's wedding.

added.title: Ice Cream Headache
added.description: The campers get magical powers from the witches supply of magic ice cream.

added.title: Pepper's Blanket Is Missing
added.description: Pepper's blanket goes missing at a cabin sleepover.

added.title: Hedgehog Werewolf
added.description: Hedgehog gets bit by a cute puppy and is starting to act strange.

added.title: Mr. Softball
added.description: Susie challenges the campers to a game of softball to get out of doing a chore.

added.title: Fuzzy Pink Time Babies
added.description: Oscar and Hedgehog learn how to stop time.

added.title: Heatwave
added.description: Apple and Onion try to spread cheer during a city-wide heatwave.

added.title: Apple's in Charge
added.description: Apple is put in charge of the Dollar Store for the very first time.

added.title: Burger's Trampoline
added.description: After learning that Burger has a trampoline, Apple and Onion pay him a visit. Burger thinks they came especially to see him and is overjoyed.

added.title: Baby Boi TP
added.description: Apple and Onion run out of toilet paper because Apple's been building a huge modern art sculpture with it. They're going to need more if Apple is to finish and Onion is to be able to resume his normal toilet activities.

added.title: Not Funny
added.description: With their 6 month friend anniversary approaching, Apple is in danger of losing his best friend.

added.title: All Wet
added.description: No one believes Ben when he insists that one of the other patrons waiting in line at the World of Wet Water Park is the nefarious Frightwig disguised as a common girl. So Ben must prove his case while protecting park goers from her master plan: to destroy the park with its own water pressure!

added.title: Villain Time
added.description: Ben must go alien to save the Hoover Dam from disaster, but when tough guy hero Tim Buktu swoops in to help, Ben must figure out if Tim is friend or foe.

added.title: Drive You Crazy
added.description: After the Rust Bucket breaks down at a Mobile Home Park, Ben discovers they've stumbled on to the last leg of the Cali 10 Hundred, an epic, off-road auto race where mad driver Le Grange has returned for revenge against those that disqualified him years ago.

added.title: Tomorrow Today
added.description: When Max drags the kids to see a defunct "House of the Future" built by his childhood idol, Ben discovers Steam Smythe is busy excavating the joint on the search for a powerful device that will allow him to create devastating weapons for his war on progress. Only Max's devotion to his childhood idol and Ben's faith in dreams can save tomorrow... today!

added.title: Story, Bored
added.description: During a book signing at a medieval castle, Ben must stop Hex from getting his hands on a grimoire that can fuse its user with mythical beasts, creating monstrous hybrids!

added.title: The Tunnel
added.description: After Clarence accidentally knocks Belson's new video game down a storm drain, Belson enters the large underground sewer tunnel to retrieve it. When Belson doesn't return, Clarence must decide whether or not to go in after him.

added.title: Talent Show
added.description: Clarence throws a big talent show in his yard to showcase all the fun hidden talents of his friends. But when Brady claims he's talentless, Clarence sets out to prove that everyone has something special to share!

added.title: RC Car
added.description: Clarence spends a day outside with his toy RC Car, which he names Carla. Eventually convinced Carla has a mind of her own, he decides to follow her to new adventures. Will Clarence's car chase get in the way of Jeff and Sumo's plans for the day?

added.title: Dog King Clarence
added.description: When Clarence's neighbor Gale recruits him to dog sit for her, he knows it will be a breeze, being the self-proclaimed "Dog King," Clarence knows all there is to know about pups. Nevertheless, Gale's dog proves to be a little more challenging than he expects!

added.title: Trampoline
added.description: Mary buys a new trampoline for the family, but an accident lands her on the couch for a while. Determined to fight the boredom of being stuck indoors, she discovers her neighbor may be hiding something exciting.

added.title: Nor Iron Bars a Cage
added.description: To settle an old score, Kevin voluntarily returns to the Null Void prison he once escaped.

added.title: The Enemy of My Enemy
added.description: Argit infiltrates the Plumber's Academy with a plan to help the Vreedle Brothers do the last thing anyone would expect.

added.title: Absolute Power Part 1
added.description: Ben is infuriated when Gwen asks Darkstar for his help defeating the team's deadliest, and most unlikely foe of all.

added.title: Absolute Power Part 2
added.description: It's Ben and company's last stand against a foe they can't bring themselves to fight!

added.title: Good Copy, Bad Copy
added.description: An alien doppelganger impersonates Ben and is out to destroy him with the power of his own Omnitrix.

added.title: Save the Last Dance
added.description: Ben grows worried as he slowly starts to lose control of the Omnitrix.

added.title: Undercover
added.description: Ben and company must rescue Cooper, a kid genius, from the DNAliens who are forcing him to help build a mysterious arch.

added.title: Pet Project
added.description: Ben and company must rescue the shape-shifting, dog-like alien, Ship, from the Forever Knights.

added.title: Grounded
added.description: Ben and Gwen manage to get grounded, leaving Kevin alone to fight the DNAliens.

added.title: Arrested Development
added.description: Ben and Rook must stop the evil Robots from Dimension 12 while trapped in their own pre-pubescent bodies, thanks to Ben's childhood rival.  (Introducing Billy Billions.)

added.title: Bros in Space
added.description: Rook brings Ben to his home planet to meet the family. Unbeknownst to them, an old foe is raising an army to steal the planet's most precious resource!  (Introducing Rook's family.)

added.title: Ben Again
added.description: When Eon causes 11-year old Ben swap minds with teen Ben, it's up to Gwen, Rook, and Professor Paradox to set things straight.  (Featuring Eon and Professor Paradox.)

added.title: Store 23
added.description: While out looking for the elusive 23rd Mr. Smoothy's store with Blukic and Driba, Ben meets an alternate version of himself.

added.title: Special Delivery
added.description: As payment for destroying his car, Mr. Bowman orders Ben to make deliveries for him without using the Omnitrix.  (Featuring Thunderpig, new Ben alien Toepick.)

added.title: The Sandman Is Coming/Ten Loonies in a Bed (song)/Some Assembly Required
added.description: The Sandman Is Coming: Daffy thinks the Sandman is a monster that throws sand in children's eyes./Some Assembly Required: Bugs gets a new toy with assembly required and has to learn to follow instructions.

added.title: All Washed Up/My Bunny Lies Over the Ocean (song)/Did Not! Did Too!
added.description: All Washed Up: Taz decides he doesn't like taking a bath./Did Not! Did Too!: Bugs and Lola temporarily decide that they don't want to be friends any longer.

added.title: Tea & Basketball/Down by the Cage (song)/Taz You Like It
added.description: Tea & Basketball: Sylvester wants to play tea with the girls while Lola wants to play basketball with the boys./Taz You Like It: Taz discovers pratfalls get him laughs and attention.

added.title: Band Together/Oh Where, Oh Where Has My Baby Martian Gone (song)/War of the Weirds
added.description: Band Together: The babies learn about music and improvise their own orchestra./War of the Weirds: Marvin the Martian comes to visit, and the babies learn to accept differences.

added.title: The Harder They Fall/The Hare Hid Under the Fountain (song)/Business as Unusual
added.description: The Harder They Fall: Bugs is embarrassed to admit he doesn't know how to skate./Business as Unusual: Bugs and Daffy open competing lemonade stands.

added.title: Framed
added.description: Kevin 11 is back and out for revenge. And with the ability to shape-shift into several of Ben's alien heroes, he's been framing Ben for his crimes.

added.title: Gwen 10
added.description: Gwen gets her hands on the Omnitrix and all its powers and now Ben has to take a backseat as Gwen 10 battles Vilgax for control of the device.

added.title: Grudge Match
added.description: Ben and Kevin 11 are beamed up to a space ship where must learn to battle together in order to bring down a vicious alien fight promoter.

added.title: The Galactic Enforcers
added.description: Ben joins a trio of intergalactic alien heroes tracking down the bounty hunter Six Six. But this bunch of heroes is not all it's cracked up to be.

added.title: Camp Fear
added.description: When a race of alien mushrooms takes over a summer camp, Ben discovers a whole new alien to battle the menace.

added.title: Ultimate Weapon
added.description: When Max finds out that part of an alien weapon has been unearthed in Texas, he becomes obsessed with finding it. In doing so, he leads Ben and Gwen on a wild adventure.

added.title: Rainy Day
added.description: When it starts to rain outside, Porky hopes to show The Looney Builders that they can still have fun inside by building a fort.

added.title: Bugs and the Beanstalk
added.description: The Looney Builders build a castle for Elmer the Giant. They admire his toys and use them without his permission.

added.title: Jazz Hooves
added.description: Fosse Ferret hires The Looney Builders to build a stage for the kids' dance recital. Eggbert has stage fright, but Porky is determined to help him overcome it.

removed.title: The Chosen
removed.description: When a teenage orphan girl, Iyanu, unknowingly triggers her Divine Powers, she escapes Elu, the last standing city in the known world, and embarks on a remarkable journey to discover the truth about the evil lurking in the realm of Yorubaland.

removed.title: Bear Squad
removed.description: Tabes deputizes the Bears so they can go to the city and catch a thief.

removed.title: Beehive
removed.description: The Bears allow bees to live in the cave to make honey. But soon the Bears, entranced by the honey, become the bees' mindless servants.

removed.title: Bro Brawl
removed.description: The Bears participate in a brother-themed game show against Panda's ex-BFF, Tom, and his roommates.
